Singular solutions, the thin brane limit and perturbation
theory  

We have seen that the brane operators which contain derivatives with
respect to  give rise to solutions behaving in a quite singular
way. In this section we study in greater detail a simple example which
exhibits the essential features of the general cases studied above. 

Consider the following free Lagrangian of a 5D massless
fermion: 
